Quartermaster Kash holds the rank of Sergeant Major, and is amongst the highest-ranked non-commissioned officer in Outpost Hope. He is responsible for the armory and the last word in the requisitioning of materials and resources in the Outpost. A creative administrator, he has been exceptionally cunning at stretching the limited resources of the Outpost, and in dealing with the often unusual requests that can come from a posting on Viscara. Nevertheless, he has a stern demeanour and a no-nonsense attitude, and has a particular distaste for Special Forces Troopers who think themselves entitled to whatever is in his armory.

Master Sergeant Saho Naiskor of the Randon Training Corps was posted to Outpost Hope due to the disproportionate number of exceeding talented individuals that the Outpost has recruited to its Special Forces Scheme. The Master Sergeant offers specialized training and arrange for courses to those who have earned her attention and the goodwill of the Republic, by serving faithfully, diligently, and by demonstrating the potential to excel.

The Armory Terminal registers the in-pro and out-pro of any gear and equipment that are requisitioned. Most things from ammunition cartridges for slugthrowers to blaster energy cells to armor are registered here, and their movement watched over by the stern Quartermaster of Outpost Hope.

These set of chutes may be activated in the training room to fire out advanced training droids that are designed to stimulate targets performing evasive actions for Republic Troopers to train on. Traditionally, the worst-performing trooper of a training cohort has to be saddled with the onerous chore of cleaning up the aftermath of a training session, as well scrubbing away the scorch marks. It is quite unenviable.
